      <h1>INTRAX GLOBAL INTERNSHIPS PROGRAM TERMS AND CONDITIONS</h1>
      <p> Intrax program, its agents, affiliates, officers, directors, staff, and representatives (collectively "Intrax") and the undersigned participant ("Participant"), understand and agree to the terms and conditions stated below relating to Participant�s participation in the Intrax Global Internship program ("Program"), Participant�s association with the company providing the internship ("Host Company") and the location of the Program ("Host Country"). </p>
      <h2>1) Participant Requirements</h2>
      <ul class="lower-latin">
        <li>Meet visa requirements and labor regulations specific to Host Country</li>
        <li>At least eighteen (18) years old upon Program start date</li>
        <li>Language skills and/or specific experience may be required depending on internship position or visa requirement</li>
        <li>Demonstrate the necessary maturity and competency to train successfully at a host company and adapt to life in an international and professional setting</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>2) Start/End Dates and Deadlines</h2>
      <ul class="lower-latin">
        <li>Applications are accepted on a rolling basis; year round (blackout dates may apply)</li>
        <li>Specific duration and start/end dates are to be determined by Intrax and the host company</li>
        <li>Participant may postpone start date (prior to matching process) within a calendar year without penalty. Date changes made by Participant after the matching process has begun or after the calendar year are subject to a reinstatement fee of $150.  For date changes after a confirmed match, refer to refund section.
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <table>
          <tr>
            <td><b>Required Participant Activity</b></td>
            <td><b>Deadline</b></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Online Application Submission</td>
            <td>80-90 days prior to departure/desired start date (depending on location and visa requirements). If requiring a visa, Participants need to allow an additional 30 days.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Application Fee Submission</td>
            <td>75-85 days prior to departure/desired start date (depending on location and visa requirements). If requiring a visa, Participants need to allow an additional 30 days.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Revised Resume and Complete Profile Submission</td>
            <td>70-80 days prior to departure/desired start date (depending on location and visa requirements). If requiring a visa, Participants need to allow an additional 30 days.</td>
          </tr>
        </table>
        </li>
        <li>Failure to meet deadlines may result in delayed start dates and/or inability to obtain necessary visas and participate on Program. </li>
      </ul>
      <h2 class="pgbr-bf">3) Responsibility of Intrax</h2>
      <p>Intrax shall be responsible and agrees to perform the following:</p>
      <ul class="lower-latin">
        <li>Upon acceptance into the Intrax Program and receipt of the Application Fee, Intrax agrees to assist Participant through the interview and match process in an internship prior to the start of the Program (with exception of J1 visa service).
          
          <div class="nested-list lower-roman">
            <div>Participants are expected to be prepared to accept the position that is offered by Intrax and the host company. Every effort will be made to accommodate preferences and requests, however, specific host companies or positions cannot be guaranteed.</div>
            <div>Participant agrees to only request interview with companies that they in good faith will accept an internship offer if made after the interview.</div>
            <div>Participant may request interview with multiple host companies but will only have a maximum of three (3) opportunities to accept an offer after the interview.</div>
            <div>There will be no Host Company replacements after a match has been made.</div>
          </div> 
        </li>
        <li>Pre-internship orientation</li>
        <li>Resume review </li>
        <li>Basic training authorization support</li>
        <li>On-program  support (inquiries related to internship position)</li>
        <li>Accident/sickness insurance (liability insurance for certain locations) (with exception of U.S. Domestic/Practical Training Program)
           <div class="nested-list lower-roman">
            <div>Participant is financially responsible for any medical expenses that are not covered by the insurance that Intrax provides.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>If Participant is seeking further program support, certain items can be added for an additional fee.  Add-on items may include:</p>
      <ul class="lower-latin">
        <li>Visa assistance (with exception of J1 visa service, which is included in Program Fee)</li>
        <li>Housing</li>
        <li>On-site orientation</li>
        <li>On-site support and regular check-ins</li>
        <li>Assistance with academic credit</li>
        <li>Any additional insurance not covered in Program Fee</li>
        <li>Airport pick-up</li>
        <li>Airport drop-off</li>
        <li>Excursions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>All Social Development Programs include:</p>
      <ul class="lower-latin">
        <li>Internship Placement</li>
        <li>Homestay with a carefully-screened host family</li>
        <li>Daily meals</li>
        <li>Health and travel insurance</li>
        <li>On-site transportation</li>
        <li>Project funding and support</li>
        <li>Basic language classes or cultural excursions</li>
        <li>24 hour emergency support</li>
      </ul>
      <p>J1 Visa Service includes:</p>
      <ul class="lower-latin">
        <li>Issuance of DS-2019 forms</li>
        <li>Travel Health Insurance</li>
        <li>Student Exchange Visitor Information System (SEVIS) fee ($180) paid by Intrax to the U.S. government</li>
        <li>Vetting your U.S. host organizations to ensure their eligibility</li>
        <li>Assisting with visa related documents</li>
        <li>Pre-departure orientation (already mentioned as a service so may not need to go here)</li>
        <li>On-program support including 24 hour emergency support</li>
      </ul>
      <h2>4) Responsibility of Participant</h2>
      <p>Participant shall be responsible and agrees to provide the following:</p>
      <ul class="lower-latin">
        <li>Transportation to/from Host Country and commuting costs
          <div class="nested-list lower-roman">
            <div>Travel itinerary is to be provided to Intrax</div>
            <div>All expenses due to flight delays/cancellations, excess baggage charges, luggage handling, and other irregularities will be the responsibility of the Participant.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>Housing in the Host Country for the length of the Program (with exception of Social Development Programs)</li>
        <li>Passports, visa fees, and all associated costs including shipping and expediting fees
          <div class="nested-list lower-roman">
            <div>Although Intrax provides visa assistance as a program add-on, it will be the responsibility of the Participant to acquire and submit all necessary documents to the appropriate consulate or government agency and to obtain the visa and/or work approval prior to the program start date.</div>
            <div>During the visa application process, passports may be required by the consulate.  It is advised that participants avoid international travel shortly before the program start date.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>Additional insurance not covered in Program Fee</li>
        <li>Medical information
          <div class="nested-list lower-roman">
            <div>Participant is responsible for providing Intrax with any personal medical information regarding health and mental conditions that may affect his/her ability to participate on Program, including but not limited to pre-existing or prior conditions, allergies, and prescription medications.</div>
            <div>Participant is required to provide Intrax with the name and contact information of the person to contact in the event of an emergency.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>Personal Responsibility
          <div class="nested-list lower-roman">
            <div>Participants are expected to behave in a professional and respectful manner throughout the duration of the Program and demonstrate open-mindedness, flexibility and a willingness to adapt. It is critical to maintain a positive attitude towards the internship, Host Company employers and coworkers, as well as the people of the host country, their culture and way of life.</div>
            <div>While Intrax provides a pre-departure orientation and safety tips, the Participant is responsible for his/her own safety and will not hold Intrax or the Host Company liable for any injuries to person or property or any other losses as a result of participation in the Program. Upon termination of the Program (for any reason), Participant is legally responsible for his/her own care, safety and legal status as an alien in the Host Country.</div>
            <div>Participant will be financially responsible for himself/herself for the duration of the program. Proof of financial means may be required as a part of the visa process.</div>
            <div>Participant agrees to use his/her best efforts for internship placement with Intrax by answering Intrax communications to ensure timely internship placement.</div>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>Participant is responsible for any civil or criminal liability or for defending against any legal claims made against them.</li>
      </ul>
